Flux and Shift are the stuns i use for 90 percent of my dungeon exp grouping where stuns work.<br>
<br>
My &quot;typical&quot; spell lineup for dungeon exp :<br>
<br>
Theft of thought<br>
Swap (default slow if no shaman, charm if there is)<br>
Some root ( i use fetter currently)<br>
AoE mezz<br>
Flux<br>
Tash<br>
Dazzle (single mezz)<br>
Shift.<br>
<br>
The reasons i still use flux and shift are two fold.   <br>
<br>
1) Chain casting flux and shift is basically free for me.  I can cast them for the entire course of a battle and only lose half a bubble of mana.  Flux is extremely fast ( 1.0 seconds i believe ), and channels through almost anything.  Shift is long enough to cast most spells i would need to cast after it, including the all important mezz ( or charm ).<br>
<br>
2) The area of effect on each spell gets larger for each new one you get.  I LIKE the small area of flux and shift.  Shift is large enough to hit most of the creatures around me, but, i dont ever have to worry about agroing things i cant see with it. Flux radius is so small, you basically have to be on top of the mob to use it.  Of course, when i am fluxing, i usually AM on top of the mob ( or its on top of me), so thats no problem.   Flux generally doesnt hit the other mezzed mobs if i am using it to chase a bounced mezz, so i am not adding agro where i dont want to be.  Stuns add agro, just like everything else we do.<br>
<br>
Of course, everything we do is situational.  When doing those damn phase spiders in DN, i use Shift and Skew.  Flux and shift dont have a wide enough range for me to reach the damn spider without being inside of it.<br>
<br>
If i am stun locking, i will go with flux and Slant.  Slant is really mana intensive, but, has a wide range and is fast in case one bounces.<br>
<br>
I am one who rarely takes AoE mezz out of his lineup when there are mobs that can be effected by it around.  Some enchanters feel it makes you lazy ( using that spell ), but, it is one of THE most overpowering spells we have when used correctly.  There is a topic on the board about AoE mezz and its uses.  Keeping AoE mezz memmed is why i dont have room for three stuns, but i always make room for 2.<br>
